    "body": "Using the default project generated by hardhat\r\n\r\n- If I fork MAINNET with default MNEMONIC it passes\r\n- If I fork RINKEBY with default MNEMONIC it fails\r\n- If I set the MNEMONIC in `hardhat.config.js` `networks.hardhat` field\r\n```\r\naccounts: {\r\n  mnemonic: process.env.MNEMONIC || \"\",\r\n},\r\n```\r\nit fails on forked MAINNET, but passes on forked RINKEBY\r\n\r\nUpdate: \r\nPerhaps the issue is hardhat forking treating the MNEMONIC to have nonce 0 when in reality the nonce is much higher... \r\nAt least for the MNEMONIC I'm using it's not 0 and shouldn't be 0 on a forked network.\r\n```\r\nconst count = await ethers.provider.getTransactionCount(deployer)\r\nconsole.log(count) // THIS IS 0\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\nSteps to reproduce:\r\n1. I first run `yarn hardhat node --fork https://<network>.infura.io/v3/<project_id>` in another window\r\n1. I then run `yarn hardhat run scripts/sample-script.js --network localhost`\r\n",
